                        <interp inst="t18420704-name-148" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM RUSHBROOK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable, No.</hi> 616.) I heard a cry of "police," and ran to the corner of Gravel-lane, and found the box in the street—I took possession of it till the officer returned with the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was going down Petticoat-lane, and a man stood at the corner with this box; he put it on my shoulder, and said, "Will you carry this for me, I will give you a drink of beer, and some half-pence?" I took it, and was following him; the witness came and took it off my shoulder.</p>
